        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Virginia is the first state to add itself to the AWB roster since
            Washington in 2023. It is the first southern state with a
            features-based AWB. And it sits inside the Fourth Circuit, which
            already <strong>upheld</strong> Maryland's ban in
            <em>Bianchi v. Brown</em> in August 2024 &mdash; en banc, 10&ndash;5.
            Federal challengers in Virginia start the case from inside the circuit
            that has already ruled against them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

